        <!-- Open Call -->
        <section class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-emerald-100">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-800 mb-6">Open Call for Submissions!</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
                <p>The Green For Sudan Science Communication Journal is thrilled to announce we are open for contributions! We invite Sudanese youth, researchers, and science enthusiasts across the globe to share their insights and help build a sustainable, scientifically informed future for our nation.</p>
                <p>As Sudan's first youth science communication journal, we believe in the power of local voices to highlight challenges, showcase innovation, and inspire action.</p>
                
                <div class="mt-8">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4 text-emerald-900">Key Areas of Focus:</h3>
                    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                        <li class="bg-emerald-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-emerald-200 font-medium flex items-center gap-2">
                            <i class="fas fa-leaf text-emerald-600"></i> Climate Change
                        </li>
                        <li class="bg-emerald-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-emerald-200 font-medium flex items-center gap-2">
                            <i class="fas fa-bolt text-emerald-600"></i> Clean & Affordable Energy
                        </li>
                        <li class="bg-emerald-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-emerald-200 font-medium flex items-center gap-2">
                            <i class="fas fa-tint text-emerald-600"></i> Clean Water & Sanitation
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <p class="mt-6">We welcome articles from all scientific disciplines and other fields of study. Contributions can address any of the UN Sustainable Development Goals, as long as they align with the journal's mission and scope.</p>
                <a href="#guidelines" class="inline-block mt-4 text-emerald-600 font-bold hover:underline">Read Submission Guidelines &rarr;</a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Platform Info -->
        <section id="guidelines" class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary border-b-2 border-emerald-500 pb-2">A Platform for Sudan's Youth</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700">We are delighted by your interest in contributing to Sudan's first youth platform dedicated to empowering young voices in science communication. This guide provides all necessary information to prepare and submit your compelling article, interview, or perspective. We aim to make complex scientific topics accessible, engaging, and highly relevant to the immediate reality of Sudanese communities.</p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-8">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Our Aims & Scope: What We Publish</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 text-sm">The Green For Sudan Journal is committed to bridging the knowledge gap in critical areas impacting Sudan's sustainable development: climate change, water security, and energy efficiency. We seek engaging, evidence-based content that:</p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5 text-gray-700">
                        <li>Translates scientific concepts into accessible language for a broad audience.</li>
                        <li>Highlights local challenges, innovations, and solutions within Sudan.</li>
                        <li>Empowers and educates our core audience: Sudanese youth and communities.</li>
                        <li>Fosters critical thinking and encourages action toward a sustainable future.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Who We Publish For (Our Audience):</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">Our primary audience consists of Sudanese youth, students, community leaders, and the general public interested in science, innovation, and sustainable development. We encourage writers to write clearly, concisely, and engagingly, avoiding overly technical jargon where possible, or explaining it in detail when necessary. Imagine you are explaining a scientific idea to an interested friend or family member.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- General Requirements -->
        <section class="bg-emerald-50 p-8 rounded-2xl">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-900 mb-8">General Submission Requirements</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-emerald-800">Originality</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">All submissions must be original work not previously published or under consideration elsewhere. We do not accept content entirely generated by AI without substantial human review and explicit declaration.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-emerald-800">Language</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">All articles must be written in clear, concise, and grammatically correct English. (We may open to other languages later).</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-emerald-800">Plagiarism</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 font-medium">We have a strict zero-tolerance policy for plagiarism. All sources must be properly cited.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-emerald-800">Tone</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">Maintain a respectful, informative, and inspiring tone. Contributions should be constructive and evidence-based.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-emerald-800">Author Bio</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">A short biography (50-100 words) highlighting your background and passion for science communication must be included.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-emerald-800">Structure</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">Use clear headings and subheadings to break up text. Keep paragraphs concise for improved readability.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Article Types -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Article Types & Guidelines</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">We accept the following article types. Click each title to expand the detailed guidelines and see what we are looking for.</p>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <!-- Perspective -->
                <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-bold text-emerald-800 hover:bg-emerald-50 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('active')">
                        Perspective / Point of View
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-sm"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content p-6 border-t border-gray-100 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                        <p><strong>What it is:</strong> A well-researched, evidence-backed argument or informed opinion piece on a scientific, policy, or societal challenge relevant to Sudan. It presents the author's viewpoint, supported by facts and analysis.</p>
                        <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To stimulate critical thinking, encourage debate, and offer new insights or potential solutions from the perspective of Sudanese youth.</p>
                        <p><strong>Key Elements:</strong> Strong thesis statement, brief background context, evidence-based arguments, potential counter-arguments addressed, and a clear call to thought/action.</p>
                        <p><strong>Target Word Count:</strong> [600-1000 words]</p>
                        <p><strong>Tone:</strong> Opinionated (evidence-based), respectful, analytical, persuasive.</p>
                        <p class="pt-2"><a href="#" class="text-emerald-600 font-bold hover:underline italic"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf mr-1"></i> Download Sample: [Perspective_Sample.pdf]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Explainer -->
                <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-bold text-emerald-800 hover:bg-emerald-50 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('active')">
                        Explainer / Digest Article
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-sm"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content p-6 border-t border-gray-100 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                        <p><strong>What it is:</strong> A concise, clear article that breaks down a specific scientific concept, new research finding, or technology into digestible information for a non-specialist audience.</p>
                        <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To demystify science, promote scientific literacy, and provide foundational understanding of key topics relevant to our pillars.</p>
                        <p><strong>Key Elements:</strong> Clear title, simple introduction defining the concept, gradual breakdown of ideas, use of analogies/metaphors, Sudan context linkage, and encouragement of simple visual aids.</p>
                        <p><strong>Target Word Count:</strong> [1000-2000 words]</p>
                        <p><strong>Tone:</strong> Clear, direct, educational, patient.</p>
                        <p class="pt-2"><a href="#" class="text-emerald-600 font-bold hover:underline italic"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf mr-1"></i> Download Sample: [Explainer_Sample.pdf]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Interview -->
                <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-bold text-emerald-800 hover:bg-emerald-50 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('active')">
                        Interview
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-sm"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content p-6 border-t border-gray-100 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                        <p><strong>What it is:</strong> A Q&A format presenting a conversation with a relevant expert, innovator, or community member about their work, insights, or experiences related to science and sustainability in Sudan.</p>
                        <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To bring diverse voices and direct expertise to our readers, offering personal insights and breaking down complex topics through dialogue.</p>
                        <p><strong>Key Elements:</strong> Brief introduction of the interviewee, formatted questions and answers, natural flow and clarity. The author must secure the interviewee's permission for publication.</p>
                        <p><strong>Target Word Count:</strong> [1000-2000 words]</p>
                        <p><strong>Tone:</strong> Conversational, informative, respectful.</p>
                        <p class="pt-2"><a href="#" class="text-emerald-600 font-bold hover:underline italic"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf mr-1"></i> Download Sample: [Interview_Sample.pdf]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Case Study -->
                <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-bold text-emerald-800 hover:bg-emerald-50 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('active')">
                        Case Study
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-sm"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content p-6 border-t border-gray-100 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                        <p><strong>What it is:</strong> A detailed examination of a specific real-world project, initiative, or problem-solving effort related to climate change, water security, or energy efficiency in Sudan. Highlights lessons learned and replicability.</p>
                        <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To showcase practical applications of scientific principles, inspire action, and provide concrete examples of sustainable development efforts.</p>
                        <p><strong>Key Elements:</strong> Problem statement, intervention/solution, brief methodology, results/outcomes, lessons learned, and future recommendations/implications.</p>
                        <p><strong>Target Word Count:</strong> [1000-2000 words]</p>
                        <p><strong>Tone:</strong> Factual, analytical, practical, inspiring.</p>
                        <p class="pt-2"><a href="#" class="text-emerald-600 font-bold hover:underline italic"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf mr-1"></i> Download Sample: [Case_Study_Sample.pdf]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Feature -->
                <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-bold text-emerald-800 hover:bg-emerald-50 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('active')">
                        Feature Article
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-sm"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content p-6 border-t border-gray-100 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                        <p><strong>What it is:</strong> An in-depth, narrative-driven exploration of a scientific topic, discovery, or issue relevant to Sudan. Feature articles often tell a story, incorporate compelling examples, and go beyond surface-level information.</p>
                        <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To engage readers with a comprehensive, yet accessible, understanding of an important scientific topic or innovation.</p>
                        <p><strong>Key Elements:</strong> Catchy title, intriguing introduction, narrative flow, context and background, examples and anecdotes, expert quotes (optional), and clear conclusion.</p>
                        <p><strong>Target Word Count:</strong> [2000-3000 words]</p>
                        <p><strong>Tone:</strong> Engaging, informative, sometimes inspiring, authoritative yet approachable.</p>
                        <p class="pt-2"><a href="#" class="text-emerald-600 font-bold hover:underline italic"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf mr-1"></i> Download Sample: [Feature_Article_Sample.pdf]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Citations -->
        <section class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Citations and References</h2>
            <p class="mb-4">Accurate citation is essential for scholarly integrity and helps our readers explore the evidence behind your claims. We use the <strong>IEEE style for references</strong>.</p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-emerald-400">Why Citation Matters:</h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
                        <li><span class="font-bold">Credibility:</span> Shows your work is grounded in reliable information and research.</li>
                        <li><span class="font-bold">Transparency:</span> Allows readers to verify information and delve deeper into topics.</li>
                        <li><span class="font-bold">Respect:</span> Gives proper credit to the original creators of ideas and data.</li>
                        <li><span class="font-bold">Learning:</span> Helps you organize your research and understand the scientific landscape.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
                    <a href="#" class="bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full font-bold transition-all flex items-center">
                        <i class="fas fa-download mr-3"></i> Download Full Citation Guide (PDF)
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- How to Submit -->
        <section class="space-y-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-primary">Ready to Submit? Here's How.</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold border-l-4 border-emerald-500 pl-4">How to Submit Your Article</h3>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border-t-4 border-emerald-500 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-200 mb-2">01</div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold mb-2 text-sm">Prepare Your Abstract</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Draft a summary of your proposed article (maximum 250 words) in English.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border-t-4 border-emerald-500 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-200 mb-2">02</div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold mb-2 text-sm">Author Biography</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Include a short biography (50-100 words) either in a separate file or within the submission form.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border-t-4 border-red-400 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-red-100 mb-2">03</div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold mb-2 text-sm">Note on Images</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-bold text-red-700">DO NOT submit images at this stage.</p>
                    <p class="text-[10px] text-gray-500 mt-1 italic">Full manuscript instructions will follow acceptance.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border-t-4 border-emerald-500 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-200 mb-2">04</div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold mb-2 text-sm">Fill Out Form</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Click the button below to navigate to our secure online portal (Google Form).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Image Guidelines -->
        <section class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-6">Images and Figures Guidelines (For Full Manuscript)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">If your article includes images, figures, or illustrations (at the later stage):</p>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex gap-4">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group text-emerald-600 mt-1"></i>
                    <div>
                        <p><strong>Separate Files:</strong> Indicate the insertion point in the text (e.g., <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1">[Insert Figure 1 Here]</code>), but upload images separately when submitting the full manuscript.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-4">
                    <i class="fas fa-copyright text-emerald-600 mt-1"></i>
                    <div>
                        <p><strong>Copyright & Licensing:</strong> Ensure you have the right to use all images. Provide credit source and licensing information for non-original work.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-4">
                    <i class="fas fa-heading text-emerald-600 mt-1"></i>
                    <div>
                        <p><strong>Captions:</strong> Provide a clear, descriptive caption for each figure, numbered sequentially (e.g., 'Figure 1: Installation of solar panels...').</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

